column2: tl;dr is the other elder millenials i know have accomplished so much and i'm all out of copium

Are there some things you never recover from? I don't know. 

I did eventually get one speaking engagement that wasn't about diversity in cannabis, from deloitte no less, and that was another happy day. I don't think that's going to happen with web3.

Or when your new boss was so excited to hire you they were willing to wait for you to have surgery, and asked you when they could tweet about it.

I don't think any amount of fame or money will ever feel as good as I did during those days.

At some point I'll know whether I'll ever hear congrats or well deserved again, or only ever be saying it to others.

The day I was promoted to Vice President was one of my happiest. One of the first ppl I met in person whilst anon said well deserved, and I'll never forget it.

Had my semi-monthly pandemic uncontrollable cry earlier today,cathartic as usual but somehow different.

I really get the feeling that this is.. it. (personally, irrespective of the world) Almost like the final bit of sorting is done and I'm just waiting to see where I've fallen.

In my own ways and spheres of influence I got to play the heroine, and as they say that's not nothing.

There's also the point that whatever the world decides should happen to you is ultimately right.
That liminal space is an exceptionally ugly one.

Chosen family has never lasted particularly long for me, because people (rightfully) are really not prepared for what they're signing up for. 

It's not really realistic at this arrested point in transition to depend on others, and I do now know that I can't do this alone.
@eigenrobot ‚ù§Ô∏è u robot

There are material reasons why that point scares me, but more than those that I think it would signify that all of this was really meaningless. That I should have found some way to fit into all of those boxes.

One of my nightmare scenarios is that something arbitrarily bad happens, I have to publicly ask for help and find out none is coming. 

Mostly I wonder what I would think and how I would feel at that point. If it would be some torrential expression or just nothing.
